Boni Says Poland Can’t Cut Social Outlays by More Than 1% of GDP

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-10-10T13:46:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/boni-says-poland-can-t-cut-social-outlays-by-more-than-1-of-gdp.html
The size of social spending in
 Poland  has been overrated and it is “not the sort of country”
where such expenditures can be cut by more than 1 percentage
point of gross domestic product,  Michal Boni , the senior adviser
to Prime Minister Donald Tusk, said today on TVN CNBC.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  